    "intro": "The movements below trace the chapter's argument pericope by pericope, asking what the narrator intends by each unit and how the units build the chapter's cumulative theological case. The central question the chapter answers is not 'what happened at En-dor?' but 'what does it look like when the covenant God withdraws from a man who has persistently chosen partial obedience, and what does that man do next?'",
